      <abstract obkms_id="48b394b7-2ef2-4626-b9e0-576ed74a5e0e" obkms_process="TRUE">
        <label>Abstract</label>
        <p><italic><tp:taxon-name obkms_id="508a636f-ac86-4fd0-8ade-bf0a87beb281" obkms_process="TRUE"><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="genus" reg="Ridleyandra">Ridleyandra</tp:taxon-name-part><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="species" reg="merohmerea">merohmerea</tp:taxon-name-part></tp:taxon-name></italic>, a new species of <tp:taxon-name obkms_id="c8859b66-c4f8-4157-8012-6dec12f97afb" obkms_process="TRUE"><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="family">Gesneriaceae</tp:taxon-name-part></tp:taxon-name>, is described and illustrated. It is endemic in Peninsular Malaysia and known from a few populations along the Tuang River in the lowland dipterocarp forest of the Ulu Galas Forest Reserve in Kelantan, Peninsular Malaysia. Its conservation status is assessed as Critically Endangered.</p>
      </abstract>
